541	Full-page caching even for logged in users	rgrp	wwaites	"The simplest way to improve performance on specific pages is to implement full page caching.

This, however, has challenges on pages with user-specific content. For example, on CKAN when a user is logged at the top of the page we have ""You are logged in as: {username}"". Similarly we change the visibility of some material depending on the status of users:

  * Visibility of Edit or Authz link on packages and groups"	enhancement	closed	awaiting triage		ckan	fixed				
